{# ── FAQ ── #}
<section class="section">
  <div class="container--narrow">
    <div class="section-header section-header--center">
      <span class="section-label">Questions</span>
      <h2>Booking FAQs</h2>
    </div>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">How do you charge for booking?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>Booking is typically charged as a percentage of the artist guarantee — usually 10–15% per confirmed show. For some projects, a flat monthly retainer makes more sense. We discuss structure openly on the first call.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">How long does it take to start getting shows?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>It depends heavily on where you are in your career and what markets we're targeting. Building relationships and routing takes time. Realistically, expect 4–8 weeks before the first confirmed dates — sometimes faster if the timing and relationships align.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">Can you get me on festival lineups?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>Festival submissions are part of the service. Whether they land depends on where you are in your career, the festival's programming needs, and timing. We'll be honest with you about what's realistic and what you need to build toward to get there.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-item__question">What if I already have some bookings happening on my own?</summary>
      <div class="faq-item__answer"><p>No problem — we can take over outreach and coordination from wherever you currently are. We'll assess what's working, what isn't, and build from there without disrupting what's already in motion.</p></div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

